    <descgrp type="add">
      <relatedmaterial>
        <head>Related Materials</head>
        <p>Researchers interested in the Chief Marshal Records may also wish to consult the commencement files in the Bentley Historical Library vertical file (call number: Fimu E3), especially "Notes on the Commencement Procession" by Joseph C. Wagner, December 15, 1936, which describes the work of the first Chief Marshals. There is also a relevant article on the responsibilities of the Chief Marshal entitled, "Conning the Campus," in the <title render="italic">Michigan Alumnus</title> Volume 37 No. 33, June 27, 1931, pg. 647.</p>
        <p>The University of Michigan Vertical File also contains files on individual classes (Class of [year], call number Fimu F99). these files contain additional commencement material.</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
